bio.experienceSummary: As a caregiver, my passion lies in nurturing the growth of young minds and making a positive impact on their lives. With a decade of experience in childcare, I have honed my skills in fostering a safe and nurturing environment for children of all ages. My approach to childcare is centered around patience, creativity, and open communication with parents. I believe in following the parents' lead when it comes to enforcing household rules and prefer to communicate regularly about their child's day. My diverse skill set includes cooking, light housekeeping, and swimming supervision, and I am certified in both First Aid and CPR. I am fluent in both English and Spanish. I enjoy engaging children in outdoor activities, board games, and educational games that stimulate their learning. I am seeking a position where I can use my skills and experience to support families and provide reliable childcare for children between the ages of 0 and 10 (open to discussing if outside of age range).

I'm excited to get to know you and your family! I'm a retired first responder looking to fill my schedule purposefully. I know just how busy life can get so if I can help a family by lending my time to care for their children as well as they would, I'd love the opportunity. 
I hope you all find amazing caretakers for your little one(s)! Baby sitter available.

description.originalText: Anita was our first attempt at a date night sitter for our 1yr old. And, it could not have been a better experience. Starting from our first phone call, Anita was warm, responsive, obviously very experienced, and put this very anxious mama at ease. Upon arrival, Anita immediately connected with our daughter and assisted with our bedtime routine. We were able to enjoy our night out knowing our daughter was in safe hands.

bio.experienceSummary:
Believe it or not, I have been babysitting for more than 12 years! I've worked with many different families and summer camps over the years, so I'm comfortable with every age group. But my most recent experiences are with infants and toddlers. 

A bit of my background...

I graduated from Tufts University in 2020 with majors in Environmental Studies and Environmental Relations (a self designed major focused on developing environmental stewardship in young people). Since graduating, I've worked as a babysitter and pet sitter, a climate justice organizer, a political canvasser, and a union organizer. 

I currently work for the NYC Department of Education as a paraprofessional for children with special needs. My goal is to become a teacher! 

As a caregiver, I like to emphasize outdoor time, music, and social-emotional learning. But my top priority is to meet each child and family where they are in order to support healthy development.

description.originalText: Caro was an incredible help to us last Summer when our childcare plans for my 1-year-old suddenly fell through. They worked with us several times a week for two months until the school year began and it was a great experience for our family. Both my baby and my 3-year-old loved Caro's energy, playfulness, and kindness. They were extremely conscientious and communicative, and we always felt comfortable knowing Caro could handle any challenge that came up and keep us fully informed if needed. (Especially during some of my toddler's most temperamental spells!) We highly recommend them as a trusted caregiver for your little ones.

bio.experienceSummary:
As a childcare provider with three years of experience, I'm passionate about supporting families and providing reliable care for their children. I've had the privilege of caring for children of various age groups, from infants to preteens. I'm comfortable enforcing household rules and communicating effectively with parents about their child's day and any issues that arise.

My patient and calm demeanor, combined with my friendly and approachable nature, allows me to connect easily with children. I enjoy engaging them in a variety of activities, including outdoor sports and physical games, board games and puzzles, and even technology-based games and apps.

I hold a college degree. I am also willing to assist with cooking, meal preparation, and light housekeeping.

I look forward to the opportunity to bring joy, support, and a sense of security to your family!

Hello my name is Lizel, I attended college for Education (birth-2nd grade) however, I have experience with all ages. I am friendly, outgoing, active, reliable, trustworthy, and fun. I am knowledgeable in child care and child education. I have 8+ years of being a nanny/babysitter. I am willing to meal prep, give dinner, bath, potty train, light housekeeping, run errands, arrange play dates, go to the park and classes. I enjoy coming up with creative activities to teach children. I am CPR certified and fully vaccinated. I am looking to join a respectable and loving family to grow with. Reference available upon request. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. Thank you

description.originalText: Lizel was wonderful! She was punctual, so nice and kind and I would definitely recommend her to anyone looking for a reliable sitter.

bio.experienceSummary: I have worked for a couple of families throughout the past 4 years. I have nannied children ranging from 6 months to 12 years old so I have experienced a variety of ages. I am a graduate of University of South Carolina, I have experience in planning day trips, chores, preparing meals, etc.

I have nannied and babysat for over several families for the past 7 years. I have babysat families in the suburbs of New Jersey to the hustle and bustle of New York City. I have taken care of babies through early teens and have taken care of twins and up to four children at a time.

Duties include meal prep, light house cleaning, transportation to and from outside school activities, homework help, bath and bed time. 

I have absolutely enjoyed spending time and getting to know every child I have taken care of. I would love to get to know you and your family and for you to get to know me a little bit more, so please do not hesitate to reach out and message me if you have any questions!

Hi, I hope you're doing well

I'm currently searching for a new opportunity to work FT starting June 2025

I'm an extremely organized and reliable bilingual nanny with over 7 years of childcare experience.
My goal as a nanny is to care, love and give the attention children deserve.

More about me and what I can provide:

* Bilingual (English & Spanish speaker)
* Organized and extremely neat
* Patient and Kind
* Planner - Love to plan Child development and age-appropriate activities /Indoor, outdoor. Enthusiast about going to museums, story times, playgrounds, setting up playdates, new adventures and always open to listen to parents suggestions/kids needs.
* Active, fun, energetic
* Problem solver
* Adaptable
* Meal preparation
* Light housekeeping ~related to the kids.
* Strong driver (NY DL)
* American Heart Association adult and pediatric/Infant CPR/AED and First Aid certificated

Happy to provide references

description.originalText: Kiara was a wonderful babysitter. She has an amazing energy with children. She knew what she was doing without much direction. She was very proactive which is a rare trait to find these days. I will definitely be reaching out to her when we are back in new york!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I'm Rachel, I'm 24 and a graduate of Connecticut College. I have nannied and babysat for multiple families over the years. I have BLS (basic life support) certification. Additionally, have experience tutoring and babysitting kids ages 0-14. I've been living in NYC for about 2 years and am about to start a full time graduate program at Columbia, so I am available for date night sitting! If you're interested feel free to reach out!

description.originalText: Rachel was fantastic with my 2 1/2 year old VERY energetic son! She showed up and within minutes was building blocks, reading books, and keeping up with him. She was able to navigate bedtime with ease!  She was incredibly professional, punctual, and all around a huge help!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! My name is Phoebe.  I'm 19 years old and just moved into Manhattan from the Westchester area. My experience with child care began when I was just 14 years old after completing a babysitting course at the prestigious West Point military base where I learned extensive CPR and child care training. I have a variety of experiences with children of all ages from 2 months- to 12-year-olds. I have an extremely magnetic personality when it comes to children and a very large heart for caring for them as well! I take pride in bringing forth the utmost excellence of care for your little one as if they were my own! I'm very flexible and easy-going and also love to cook and clean so I'm able to provide any extra help around the house if needed! Your child's safety and happiness is my priority!
